en_194311_0	31 individuals admitted to hospital after they got injured as elephants went on a rampage at the Mihindu Perahera in Kahawatta.
en_194311_1	The Police Media Spokesperson noted that 19 women and 12 men were injured in the incident.
en_194311_2	An on-duty police officer at the Perehera was also injured and admitted to the Ratnapura hospital.
en_194311_3	One of the elephants taking part in the Perehara had first gone berserk and few other elephants joined it creating a chaotic situation.
